description: Registeel was imprisoned by people in ancient times. The metal composing its body is thought to be a curious substance that is not of this earth.

name: Latias
description: Latias is highly intelligent and capable of understanding human speech. It is covered with a glass-like down. The Pokémon enfolds its body with its down and refracts light to alter its appearance.

name: Latios
description: Latios will only open its heart to a Trainer with a compassionate spirit. This Pokémon can fly faster than a jet plane by folding its forelegs to minimize air resistance.

name: Kyogre
description: Kyogre is said to be the personification of the sea itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Groudon, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

name: Groudon
description: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

name: Rayquaza
description: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

name: Jirachi
description: Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

name: Deoxys
description: Deoxys emerged from a virus that came from space. It is highly intelligent and wields psychokinetic powers. This Pokémon shoots lasers from the crystalline organ on its chest.

name: Turtwig
description: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

name: Grotle
description: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

name: Torterra
description: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

name: Chimchar
description: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

name: Monferno
description: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.

name: Infernape
description: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

name: Piplup
description: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: Prinplup
description: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

name: Empoleon
description: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

name: Starly
description: They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

name: Staravia
description: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.

name: Staraptor
description: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor, they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

name: Bidoof
description: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

name: Bibarel
description: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

name: Kricketot
description: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

name: Kricketune
description: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

name: Shinx
description: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: Luxio
description: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

name: Luxray
description: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

name: Budew
description: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

name: Roserade
description: With the movements of a dancer, it strikes with whips that are densely lined with poison thorns.

name: Cranidos
description: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

name: Rampardos
description: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

name: Shieldon
description: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

name: Bastiodon
description: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

name: Burmy
description: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

name: Wormadam
description: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: Mothim
description: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

name: Combee
description: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.

name: Vespiquen
description: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by Combee.

name: Pachirisu
description: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

name: Buizel
description: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

name: Floatzel
description: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

name: Cherubi
description: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

name: Cherrim
description: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun's rays with its whole body.

name: Shellos
description: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.

name: Gastrodon
description: It apparently had a huge shell for protection in ancient times. It lives in shallow tidal pools.

name: Ambipom
description: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

name: Drifloon
description: These Pokémon are called the "Signpost for Wandering Spirits." Children holding them sometimes vanish.

name: Drifblim
description: It's drowsy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

name: Buneary
description: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.

name: Lopunny
description: The ears appear to be delicate. If they are touched roughly, it kicks with its graceful legs.

name: Mismagius
description: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

name: Honchkrow
description: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous Murkrow in tow.

name: Glameow
description: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

name: Purugly
description: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

name: Chingling
description: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

name: Stunky
description: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

name: Skuntank
description: It sprays a stinky fluid from its tail. The fluid smells worse the longer it is allowed to fester.

name: Bronzor
description: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

name: Bronzong
description: Ancient people believed that petitioning Bronzong for rain was the way to make crops grow.

name: Bonsly
description: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

name: Mime Jr.
description: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

name: Happiny
description: It carefully carries a round, white rock that it thinks is an egg. It's bothered by how curly its hair looks.

name: Chatot
description: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: Spiritomb
description: It was bound to a fissure in an odd keystone as punishment for misdeeds 500 years ago.

name: Gible
description: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

name: Gabite
description: As it digs to expand its nest, it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.

name: Garchomp
description: It flies at speeds equal to a jet fighter plane. It never allows its prey to escape.

name: Munchlax
description: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.

name: Riolu
description: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

name: Lucario
description: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

name: Hippopotas
description: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.

name: Hippowdon
description: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

name: Skorupi
description: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

name: Drapion
description: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

name: Croagunk
description: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

name: Toxicroak
description: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

name: Carnivine
description: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

name: Finneon
description: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

name: Lumineon
description: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

name: Mantyke
description: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean, people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.

name: Snover
description: In the spring, it grows berries with the texture of frozen treats around its belly.

name: Abomasnow
description: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

name: Weavile
description: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

name: Magnezone
description: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

name: Lickilicky
description: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.

name: Rhyperior
description: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. Geodude are shot at rare times.

name: Tangrowth
description: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

name: Electivire
description: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

name: Magmortar
description: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.

name: Togekiss
description: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.

name: Yanmega
description: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

name: Leafeon
description: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

name: Glaceon
description: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

name: Gliscor
description: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

name: Mamoswine
description: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

name: Porygon-Z
description: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

name: Gallade
description: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

name: Probopass
description: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

name: Dusknoir
description: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

name: Froslass
description: Legends in snowy regions say that a woman who was lost on an icy mountain was reborn as Froslass.

name: Rotom
description: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

name: Uxie
description: It is said that its emergence gave humans the intelligence to improve their quality of life.

name: Mesprit
description: It sleeps at the bottom of a lake. Its spirit is said to leave its body to fly on the lake's surface.

name: Azelf
description: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

name: Dialga
description: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

name: Palkia
description: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

name: Heatran
description: Boiling blood, like magma, circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

name: Regigigas
description: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: Giratina
description: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

name: Cresselia
description: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
description: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

name: Manaphy
description: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Darkrai
description: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Shaymin
description: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

name: Arceus
description: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

name: Victini
description: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.

name: Snivy
description: They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.

name: Servine
description: When it gets dirty, its leaves can't be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

name: Serperior
description: It can stop its opponents' movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

name: Tepig
description: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

name: Pignite
description: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: Emboar
description: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

name: Oshawott
description: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: Dewott
description: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

name: Samurott
description: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

name: Patrat
description: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

name: Watchog
description: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: Lillipup
description: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it's also smart enough to check its foe's strength and avoid battle.

name: Herdier
description: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

name: Stoutland
description: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.

name: Purrloin
description: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can't help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

name: Liepard
description: Stealthily, it sneaks up on its target, striking from behind before its victim has a chance to react.

name: Pansage
description: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

name: Simisage
description: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Pansear
description: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Simisear
description: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

name: Panpour
description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: Simipour
description: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: Munna
description: It eats the dreams of people and Pokémon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.

name: Musharna
description: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

name: Pidove
description: These Pokémon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.

name: Tranquill
description: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

name: Unfezant
description: Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.

name: Blitzle
description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

name: Zebstrika
description: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: Roggenrola
description: They were discovered a hundred years ago in an earthquake fissure. Inside each one is an energy core.

name: Boldore
description: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swiftly moves front to back and left to right.

name: Gigalith
description: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

name: Woobat
description: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

name: Swoobat
description: Anyone who comes into contact with the ultrasonic waves emitted by a courting male experiences a positive mood shift.

name: Drilbur
description: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.

name: Excadrill
description: More than 300 feet below the surface, they build mazelike nests. Their activity can be destructive to subway tunnels.

name: Audino
description: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

name: Timburr
description: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

name: Gurdurr
description: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: Conkeldurr
description: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

name: Tympole
description: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans. It uses the rhythm of these sounds to talk.

name: Palpitoad
description: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.

name: Seismitoad
description: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

name: Throh
description: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

name: Sawk
description: Tying their belts gets them pumped and makes their punches more destructive. Disturbing their training angers them.

name: Sewaddle
description: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

name: Swadloon
description: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

name: Leavanny
description: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

name: Venipede
description: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

name: Whirlipede
description: It is usually motionless, but when attacked, it rotates at high speed and then crashes into its opponent.

name: Scolipede
description: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

name: Cottonee
description: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

name: Whimsicott
description: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

name: Petilil
description: Since they prefer moist, nutrient-rich soil, the areas where Petilil live are known to be good for growing plants.

name: Lilligant
description: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

name: Basculin
description: Its temperament is vicious and aggressive. This Pokémon is also full of vitality and can multiply rapidly before anyone notices.

name: Sandile
description: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

name: Krokorok
description: The special membrane covering its eyes can sense the heat of objects, so it can see its surroundings even in darkness.

name: Krookodile
description: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

name: Darumaka
description: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Darmanitan
description: Its internal fire burns at 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

name: Maractus
description: Arid regions are their habitat. They move rhythmically, making a sound similar to maracas.

name: Dwebble
description: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

name: Crustle
description: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

name: Scraggy
description: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.

name: Scrafty
description: It can smash concrete blocks with its kicking attacks. The one with the biggest crest is the group leader.

name: Sigilyph
description: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

name: Yamask
description: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

name: Cofagrigus
description: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

name: Tirtouga
description: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: Carracosta
description: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.

name: Archen
description: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

name: Archeops
description: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.

name: Trubbish
description: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: Garbodor
description: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

name: Zorua
description: To protect themselves from danger, they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pokémon.

name: Zoroark
description: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

name: Minccino
description: These Pokémon prefer a tidy habitat. They are always sweeping and dusting, using their tails as brooms.

name: Cinccino
description: Cinccino's body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

name: Gothita
description: They intently observe both Trainers and Pokémon. Apparently, they are looking at something that only Gothita can see.

name: Gothorita
description: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

name: Gothitelle
description: They can predict the future from the placement and movement of the stars. They can see Trainers' life spans.

name: Solosis
description: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: Duosion
description: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

name: Reuniclus
description: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: Ducklett
description: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

name: Swanna
description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

name: Vanillite
description: This Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. It sleeps buried in snow.

name: Vanillish
description: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon's habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

name: Vanilluxe
description: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.

name: Deerling
description: The turning of the seasons changes the color and scent of this Pokémon's fur. People use it to mark the seasons.

name: Sawsbuck
description: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

name: Emolga
description: The energy made in its cheeks' electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

name: Karrablast
description: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

name: Escavalier
description: These Pokémon evolve by wearing the shell covering of a Shelmet. The steel armor protects their whole body.

name: Foongus
description: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball, then releases poison spores.

name: Amoonguss
description: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

name: Frillish
description: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

name: Jellicent
description: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent's habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

name: Alomomola
description: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

name: Joltik
description: They attach themselves to large-bodied Pokémon and absorb static electricity, which they store in an electric pouch.

name: Galvantula
description: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: Ferroseed
description: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

name: Ferrothorn
description: They attach themselves to cave ceilings, firing steel spikes at targets passing beneath them.

name: Klink
description: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

name: Klang
description: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn't return, it will die.

name: Klinklang
description: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

name: Tynamo
description: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

name: Eelektrik
description: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

name: Eelektross
description: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: Elgyem
description: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.

name: Beheeyem
description: It uses psychic power to control an opponent's brain and tamper with its memories.

name: Litwick
description: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

name: Lampent
description: It arrives near the moment of death and steals spirit from the body.

name: Chandelure
description: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

name: Axew
description: They mark their territory by leaving gashes in trees with their tusks. If a tusk breaks, a new one grows in quickly.

name: Fraxure
description: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

name: Haxorus
description: Their sturdy tusks will stay sharp even if used to cut steel beams. These Pokémon are covered in hard armor.

name: Cubchoo
description: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

name: Beartic
description: It freezes its breath to create fangs and claws of ice to fight with. Cold northern areas are its habitat.

name: Cryogonal
description: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Shelmet
description: It evolves when bathed in an electric-like energy along with Karrablast. The reason is still unknown.

name: Accelgor
description: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

name: Stunfisk
description: It conceals itself in the mud of the seashore. Then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.

name: Mienfoo
description: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: Mienshao
description: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

name: Druddigon
description: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

name: Golett
description: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It's been active for thousands of years.

name: Golurk
description: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

name: Pawniard
description: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.

name: Bisharp
description: Bisharp pursues prey in the company of a large group of Pawniard. Then Bisharp finishes off the prey.

name: Bouffalant
description: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

name: Rufflet
description: They will challenge anything, even strong opponents, without fear. Their frequent fights help them become stronger.

name: Braviary
description: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

name: Vullaby
description: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

name: Mandibuzz
description: Watching from the sky, they swoop to strike weakened Pokémon on the ground. They decorate themselves with bones.

name: Heatmor
description: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

name: Durant
description: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

name: Deino
description: Lacking sight, it's unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

name: Zweilous
description: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

name: Hydreigon
description: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!

name: Larvesta
description: The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.

name: Volcarona
description: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona's fire provided a replacement for the sun.

name: Cobalion
description: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

name: Terrakion
description: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

name: Virizion
description: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

name: Tornadus
description: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

name: Thundurus
description: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

name: Reshiram
description: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

name: Zekrom
description: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.

name: Landorus
description: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

name: Kyurem
description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

name: Keldeo
description: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

name: Meloetta
description: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

name: Genesect
description: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

name: Chespin
description: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.

name: Quilladin
description: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

name: Chesnaught
description: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

name: Fennekin
description: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.

name: Braixen
description: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

name: Delphox
description: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.

name: Froakie
description: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

name: Frogadier
description: Its swiftness is unparalleled. It can scale a tower of more than 2,000 feet in a minute's time.

name: Greninja
description: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

name: Bunnelby
description: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

name: Diggersby
description: As powerful as an excavator, its ears can reduce dense bedrock to rubble. When it's finished digging, it lounges lazily.

name: Fletchling
description: Despite the beauty of its lilting voice, it's merciless to intruders that enter its territory.

name: Fletchinder
description: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.

name: Talonflame
description: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.

name: Scatterbug
description: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

name: Spewpa
description: The beaks of bird Pokémon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

name: Vivillon
description: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

name: Litleo
description: They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.

name: Pyroar
description: With fiery breath of more than 10,000 degrees Fahrenheit, they viciously threaten any challenger. The females protect the pride's cubs.

name: Flabebe
description: This Pokémon can draw forth the power hidden within blooming wild flowers. It is particularly fond of red flowers.

name: Floette
description: This Pokémon draws forth what power is left in withered flowers to make them healthy again. It holds a red flower.

name: Florges
description: This Pokémon creates an impressive flower garden in its territory. It draws forth the power of the red flowers around its neck.

name: Skiddo
description: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.

name: Gogoat
description: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.

name: Pancham
description: It does its level best to glare and pull a scary face, but it can't help grinning if anyone pats its head.

name: Pangoro
description: It charges ahead and bashes its opponents like a berserker, uncaring about any hits it might take. Its arms are mighty enough to snap a telephone pole.

name: Furfrou
description: Left alone, its fur will grow longer and longer, but it will only allow someone it trusts to cut it.

name: Espurr
description: It has enough psychic energy to blast everything within 300 feet of itself, but it has no control over its power.

name: Meowstic
description: The eyeball patterns on the interior of its ears emit psychic energy. It keeps the patterns tightly covered because that power is too immense.

name: Honedge
description: If anyone dares to grab its hilt, it wraps a blue cloth around that person's arm and drains that person's life energy completely.

name: Doublade
description: The complex attack patterns of its two swords are unstoppable, even for an opponent greatly accomplished at swordplay.

name: Aegislash
description: Apparently, it can detect the innate qualities of leadership. According to legend, whoever it recognizes is destined to become king.

name: Spritzee
description: In the past, rather than using perfume, royal ladies carried a Spritzee that would waft a fragrance they liked.

name: Aromatisse
description: Its scent is so overpowering that, unless a Trainer happens to really enjoy the smell, he or she will have a hard time walking alongside it.

name: Swirlix
description: Because it eats nothing but sweets, its fur is as sticky sweet as cotton candy.

name: Slurpuff
description: Its sense of smell is 100 million times better than a human's, so even the faintest scent tells it about everything in the area. It's like it can see with its nose!

name: Inkay
description: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.

name: Malamar
description: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

name: Binacle
description: They stretch and then contract, yanking their rocks along with them in bold hops. They eat seaweed that washes up on the shoreline.

name: Barbaracle
description: Barbaracle's legs and hands have minds of their own, and they will move independently. But they usually follow the head's orders.

name: Skrelp
description: It looks just like rotten kelp. It hides from foes while storing up power for its evolution.

name: Dragalge
description: Tales are told of ships that wander into seas where Dragalge live, never to return.

name: Clauncher
description: Through controlled explosions of internal gas, it can expel water like a pistol shot. At close distances, it can shatter rock.

name: Clawitzer
description: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

name: Helioptile
description: The frills on either side of its head have cells that generate electricity when exposed to sunlight.

name: Heliolisk
description: It stimulates its muscles with electricity, boosting the strength in its legs and enabling it to run 100 yards in five seconds.

name: Tyrunt
description: Its immense jaws have enough destructive force that it can chew up an automobile. It lived 100 million years ago.

name: Tyrantrum
description: Nothing could stop this Pokémon 100 million years ago, so it behaved like a king.

name: Amaura
description: This calm Pokémon lived in a cold land where there were no violent predators like Tyrantrum.

name: Aurorus
description: Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent's attack.

name: Sylveon
description: It wraps its ribbonlike feelers around the arm of its beloved Trainer and walks with him or her.

name: Hawlucha
description: With its wings, it controls its position in the air. It likes to attack from above, a maneuver that is difficult to defend against.

name: Dedenne
description: It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.

name: Carbink
description: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

name: Goomy
description: It's covered in a slimy membrane that makes any punches or kicks slide off it harmlessly.

name: Sliggoo
description: Its four horns are a high-performance radar system. It uses them to sense sounds and smells, rather than using ears or a nose.

name: Goodra
description: It attacks with retractable horns. It throws a punch that's the equivalent of the force of a hundred pro boxers.

name: Klefki
description: It never lets go of a key that it likes, so people give it the keys to vaults and safes as a way to prevent crime.

name: Phantump
description: According to old tales, these Pokémon are stumps possessed by the spirits of children who died while lost in the forest.

name: Trevenant
description: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It's kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.

name: Pumpkaboo
description: It is said to carry wandering spirits to the place where they belong so they can move on.

name: Gourgeist
description: It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.

name: Bergmite
description: Using air of -150 degrees Fahrenheit, they freeze opponents solid. They live in herds above the snow line on mountains.

name: Avalugg
description: The way several Bergmite huddle on its back makes it look like an aircraft carrier made of ice.

name: Noibat
description: Even a robust wrestler will become dizzy and unable to stand when exposed to its 200,000-hertz ultrasonic waves.

name: Noivern
description: The ultrasonic waves it emits from its ears can reduce a large boulder to pebbles. It swoops out of the dark to attack.

name: Xerneas
description: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

name: Yveltal
description: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

name: Zygarde
description: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.

name: Diancie
description: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

name: Hoopa
description: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

name: Volcanion
description: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

name: Rowlet
description: It feels relaxed in tight, dark places and has been known to use its Trainer's pocket or bag as a nest.

name: Dartrix
description: Supremely sensitive to the presence of others, it can detect opponents standing behind it, flinging its sharp feathers to take them out.

name: Decidueye
description: Decidueye can nock and fire an arrow at an enemy in a tenth of a second, so its battles are decided in the blink of an eye.

name: Litten
description: Its coat regrows twice a year. When the time comes, Litten sets its own body on fire and burns away the old fur.

name: Torracat
description: When its mane is standing on end, you can tell it's feeling good. When it isn't feeling well, its fur will lie down flat.

name: Incineroar
description: When its fighting spirit is set alight, the flames around its waist become especially intense.

name: Popplio
description: Popplio gets on top of its bouncy water balloons to jump higher. It's quite the acrobatic fighter!

name: Brionne
description: It attacks by smacking its enemies with the exploding water balloons that it creates.

name: Primarina
description: Also known as a songstress, it has a fantastical look on moonlit nights when it leads its colony in song.

name: Pikipek
description: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!

name: Trumbeak
description: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.

name: Toucannon
description: Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.

name: Yungoos
description: Although it will eat anything, it prefers fresh living things, so it marches down streets in search of prey.

name: Gumshoos
description: Patient by nature, this Pokémon loses control of itself and pounces when it spots its favorite meal—Rattata!

name: Grubbin
description: It spits a sticky thread to stop opponents in their tracks, and then it grabs them in its sharp, sturdy mandibles to take them down.

name: Charjabug
description: Its stout shell provides excellent defense from attacks. It uses electricity on persistent opponents.

name: Vikavolt
description: Vikavolt flusters opponents with acrobatic flying maneuvers. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electric beam attack.

name: Crabrawler
description: Crabrawler has been known to mistake Exeggutor for a coconut tree and climb it. The enraged Exeggutor shakes it off and stomps it.

name: Crabominable
description: Before it stops to think, it just starts pummeling. There are records of its turning back avalanches with a flurry of punches.

name: Oricorio
description: This Oricorio has drunk red nectar. If its Trainer gives the wrong order, this passionate Pokémon becomes fiercely angry.

name: Cutiefly
description: Cutiefly can pick up the auras of living things. It skillfully reads those auras to predict its foes' movements and make fools of them.

name: Ribombee
description: It can predict the weather from moisture levels and wind direction. Ribombee only reveals itself when there are a few clear days in a row.

name: Rockruff
description: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!

name: Lycanroc
description: The rocks in its mane are sharper than a knife. Fragments that break off are treasured as good luck charms.

name: Wishiwashi
description: When it's in a jam, its shining eyes attract others of its kind. The light from its eyes is visible almost 25 miles away.

name: Mareanie
description: Aside from its head, its body parts regenerate quickly if they're cut off. After a good night's sleep, Mareanie is back to normal.

name: Toxapex
description: With its 12 legs, it creates a dome to shelter within. The flow of the tides doesn't affect Toxapex in there, so it's very comfortable.

name: Mudbray
description: Possessing mighty power, Mudbray can be loaded with 50 times its own body weight and will be totally fine.

name: Mudsdale
description: It can trudge mountain roads without rest for three days and three nights, all the while dragging a 10-ton load.

name: Dewpider
description: It can only breathe oxygen that has dissolved in water, so it wears a water bubble on its head when it walks around on land.

name: Araquanid
description: It has a habit of storing things it values in its water bubble. If its Trainer doesn't watch out, Araquanid will try to put them in its bubble!

name: Fomantis
description: It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.

name: Lurantis
description: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it's dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokémon.

name: Morelull
description: It likes damp dark places. When night falls, the spores filling the caps of its mushrooms glow.

name: Shiinotic
description: When it starts fighting for territory with Parasect, the entire area gets completely coated in spores!

name: Salandit
description: It weakens opponents and sends them reeling with its poisonous gas. Salandit doesn't deal well with Spinda, since it's always reeling.

name: Salazzle
description: It punishes Salandit that couldn't bring it food with a fierce slap of its flame-spewing palm.

name: Stufful
description: Stufful hates to be hugged or touched in any way. It will squirm, thrash, and resist with amazing power.

name: Bewear
description: It waves its hands wildly in intimidation and warning. Life is over for anyone who doesn't run away as fast as possible.

name: Bounsweet
description: It tries to resist being swallowed by a bird Pokémon by spinning the sepals on its head. It's usually a fruitless attempt.

name: Steenee
description: It bounces around, swinging the sepals on its head with abandon. They're quite painful when they smack you!

name: Tsareena
description: A Pokémon with an aggressive personality and a mastery of kicking, it cackles every time it kicks an opponent.

name: Comfey
description: It picks flowers and sticks them to its body with fluids it produces. The aroma that wafts from its petals has a healing effect.

name: Oranguru
description: Oranguru don't get along with each other, so they're always engaging in battles of wits to decide which one is superior.

name: Passimian
description: Berries are its weapons as well as the staple of its diet. The one that can throw a berry the farthest is the boss of the troop.

name: Wimpod
description: An astonishingly cowardly Pokémon, Wimpod will whir its legs at high speeds to run away if anything comes near it.

name: Golisopod
description: Its claws, which it can extend and retract at will, are its greatest weapons. Golisopod is sometimes accompanied by Wimpod.

name: Sandygast
description: If you build sand mounds when you're playing, destroy them before you go home, or they may get possessed and become Sandygast.

name: Palossand
description: Once it has whipped up a sandstorm to halt its opponents in their tracks, this terrifying Pokémon snatches away their vitality.

name: Pyukumuku
description: Its entire body is covered in its own slime. If you accidentally step on one, you'll slip, and it will get mad and smack you!

name: Type: Null
description: There's danger of its going on a rampage, so its true power is sealed away beneath its control mask.

name: Silvally
description: Through the bond it formed with its Trainer, its will was strengthened, and it was able to destroy its control mask.

name: Minior
description: This is its form when its shell has fallen off. The color of its core depends on the materials that made up the food it ate.

name: Komala
description: It remains asleep from birth to death as a result of the sedative properties of the leaves that form its diet.

name: Turtonator
description: Its exploding shell poses a real danger but is sensitive to moisture. On rainy days, Turtonator takes silent refuge in caves.

name: Togedemaru
description: Its capacity to produce electricity is somewhat limited, so it gets charged up by letting lightning strike it!

name: Mimikyu
description: A gust of wind revealed what hides under this Pokémon's rag to a passing Trainer, who went home and died painfully that very night.

name: Bruxish
description: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie's spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.

name: Drampa
description: It appears in towns and plays with the children. Drampa will protect kids when they're in danger, so their moms don't have to worry.

name: Dhelmise
description: Its chain-like green seaweed can stretch outward for hundreds of yards. For some reason, it gets along well with Skrelp.

name: Jangmo-o
description: It will never show an enemy its back in battle. Ancient warriors liked Jangmo-o for its valiant disposition and made it one of their own.

name: Hakamo-o
description: The scales it sheds can be molded and processed to make pots and pans. They conduct heat well, so they're a popular item.

name: Kommo-o
description: It battles valiantly with its fists, which are armored in steel scales. Kommo-o specializes in uppercuts.

name: Tapu Koko
description: The lightning-wielding guardian deity of Melemele, Tapu Koko is brimming with curiosity and appears before people from time to time.

name: Tapu Lele
description: Although called a guardian deity, Tapu Lele is devoid of guilt about its cruel disposition and can be described as nature incarnate.

name: Tapu Bulu
description: It makes ringing sounds with its tail to let others know where it is, avoiding unneeded conflicts. This guardian deity of Ula'ula controls plants.

name: Tapu Fini
description: Although it's called a guardian deity, terrible calamities sometimes befall those who recklessly approach Tapu Fini.

name: Cosmog
description: Whether or not it's a Pokémon from this world is a mystery. When it's in a jam, it warps away to a safe place to hide.

name: Cosmoem
description: As it absorbs light, Cosmoem continues to grow. Its golden shell is surprisingly solid.

name: Solgaleo
description: In writings from the distant past, it's called by the name "the beast that devours the sun."

name: Lunala
description: It sometimes summons unknown powers and life-forms here to this world from holes that lead to other worlds.

name: Nihilego
description: A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

name: Buzzwole
description: Buzzwole goes around showing off its abnormally swollen muscles. It is one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: Pheromosa
description: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Xurkitree
description: They've been dubbed Ultra Beasts. Some of them stand unmoving, like trees, with their arms and legs stuck into the ground.

name: Celesteela
description: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Kartana
description: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Guzzlord
description: An unknown life-form called a UB. It may be constantly hungry—it is certainly always devouring something.

name: Necrozma
description: Light is the source of its energy. If it isn't devouring light, impurities build up in it and on it, and Necrozma darkens and stops moving.

name: Magearna
description: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

name: Marshadow
description: It sinks into the shadows of people and Pokémon, where it can understand their feelings and copy their capabilities.

name: Poipole
description: An Ultra Beast that lives in a different world, it cackles wildly as it sprays its opponents with poison from the needles on its head.

name: Naganadel
description: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

name: Stakataka
description: When stone walls started moving and attacking, the brute's true identity was this mysterious life-form, which brings to mind an Ultra Beast.

name: Blacephalon
description: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It's apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: Zeraora
description: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.

name: Meltan
description: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

name: Melmetal
description: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

name: Grookey
description: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.

name: Thwackey
description: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.

name: Rillaboom
description: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.

name: Scorbunny
description: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokémon's body. Once that happens, it's ready to fight at full power.

name: Raboot
description: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

name: Cinderace
description: It juggles a pebble with its feet, turning it into a burning soccer ball. Its shots strike opponents hard and leave them scorched.

name: Sobble
description: When scared, this Pokémon cries. Its tears pack the chemical punch of 100 onions, and attackers won't be able to resist weeping.

name: Drizzile
description: A clever combatant, this Pokémon battles using water balloons created with moisture secreted from its palms.

name: Inteleon
description: It has many hidden capabilities, such as fingertips that can shoot water and a membrane on its back that it can use to glide through the air.

name: Skwovet
description: It stores berries in its cheeks. When there are no berries to be found, Skwovet will stuff pebbles into its cheeks to stave off its cravings.

name: Greedent
description: It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn't notice the loss.

name: Rookidee
description: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

name: Corvisquire
description: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.

name: Corviknight
description: Although its wings have partly turned to steel and become heavy as a result, this Pokémon flies through the skies with ease.

name: Blipbug
description: A constant collector of information, this Pokémon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn't.

name: Dottler
description: It barely moves, but it's still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

name: Orbeetle
description: It's famous for its high level of intelligence, and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

name: Nickit
description: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokémon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

name: Thievul
description: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

name: Gossifleur
description: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

name: Eldegoss
description: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

name: Wooloo
description: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

name: Dubwool
description: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You'll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

name: Chewtle
description: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.

name: Drednaw
description: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.

name: Yamper
description: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

name: Boltund
description: This Pokémon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

name: Rolycoly
description: Most of its body has the same composition as coal. Fittingly, this Pokémon was first discovered in coal mines about 400 years ago.

name: Carkol
description: The temperature inside its body increases when it experiences strong emotions. It rolls around frantically while spewing flames.

name: Coalossal
description: It's usually peaceful, but the vandalism of mines enrages it. Offenders will be incinerated with flames that reach 2,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Applin
description: It spends its entire life inside an apple. It hides from its natural enemies, bird Pokémon, by pretending it's just an apple and nothing more.

name: Flapple
description: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.

name: Appletun
description: Eating a sweet apple caused its evolution. A nectarous scent wafts from its body, luring in the bug Pokémon it preys on.

name: Silicobra
description: As it digs, it swallows sand and stores it in its neck pouch. The pouch can hold more than 17 pounds of sand.

name: Sandaconda
description: When it contracts its body, over 220 pounds of sand sprays from its nose. If it ever runs out of sand, it becomes disheartened.

name: Cramorant
description: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.

name: Arrokuda
description: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It's very proud of that jaw.

name: Barraskewda
description: This Pokémon has a jaw that's as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda's flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.

name: Toxel
description: It stores poison in an internal poison sac and secretes that poison through its skin. If you touch this Pokémon, a tingling sensation follows.

name: Toxtricity
description: When this Pokémon sounds as if it's strumming a guitar, it's actually clawing at the protrusions on its chest to generate electricity.

name: Sizzlipede
description: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

name: Centiskorch
description: When it heats up, its body temperature reaches about 1,500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

name: Clobbopus
description: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

name: Grapploct
description: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

name: Sinistea
description: This Pokémon is said to have been born when a lonely spirit possessed a cold, leftover cup of tea.

name: Polteageist
description: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.

name: Hatenna
description: Via the protrusion on its head, it senses other creatures' emotions. If you don't have a calm disposition, it will never warm up to you.

name: Hattrem
description: No matter who you are, if you bring strong emotions near this Pokémon, it will silence you violently.

name: Hatterene
description: It emits psychic power strong enough to cause headaches as a deterrent to the approach of others.

name: Impidimp
description: Through its nose, it sucks in the emanations produced by people and Pokémon when they feel annoyed. It thrives off this negative energy.

name: Morgrem
description: When it gets down on all fours as if to beg for forgiveness, it's trying to lure opponents in so that it can stab them with its spear-like hair.

name: Grimmsnarl
description: With the hair wrapped around its body helping to enhance its muscles, this Pokémon can overwhelm even Machamp.

name: Obstagoon
description: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.

name: Perrserker
description: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.

name: Cursola
description: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokémon's core spirit.

name: Sirfetch’d
description: Only Farfetch'd that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokémon's leek withers, it will retire from combat.

name: Mr. Rime
description: It's highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

name: Runerigus
description: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask, the painting began to move.

name: Milcery
description: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.

name: Alcremie
description: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.

name: Falinks
description: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

name: Pincurchin
description: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.

name: Snom
description: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.

name: Frosmoth
description: Icy scales fall from its wings like snow as it flies over fields and mountains. The temperature of its wings is less than −290 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Stonjourner
description: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

name: Eiscue
description: It drifted in on the flow of ocean waters from a frigid place. It keeps its head iced constantly to make sure it stays nice and cold.

name: Indeedee
description: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.

name: Morpeko
description: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokémon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.

name: Cufant
description: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

name: Copperajah
description: They came over from another region long ago and worked together with humans. Their green skin is resistant to water.

name: Dracozolt
description: In ancient times, it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body, but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

name: Arctozolt
description: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

name: Dracovish
description: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

name: Arctovish
description: Though it's able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings, it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

name: Duraludon
description: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

name: Dreepy
description: After being reborn as a ghost Pokémon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.

name: Drakloak
description: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

name: Dragapult
description: When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.

name: Zacian
description: Known as a legendary hero, this Pokémon absorbs metal particles, transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

name: Zamazenta
description: In times past, it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

name: Eternatus
description: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

name: Kubfu
description: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

name: Urshifu
description: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

name: Zarude
description: Within dense forests, this Pokémon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It's incredibly aggressive, and the other Pokémon of the forest fear it.

name: Regieleki
description: This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It's said that removing the rings on Regieleki's body will unleash the Pokémon's latent power.

name: Regidrago
description: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago's arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokémon. The theory remains unproven.

name: Glastrier
description: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It's also a belligerent Pokémon—anything it wants, it takes by force.

name: Spectrier
description: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn't use its sense of sight. Spectrier's kicks are said to separate soul from body.

name: Calyrex
description: Calyrex is a merciful Pokémon, capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

name: Wyrdeer
description: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokémon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

name: Kleavor
description: Parts of its body turned to stone when it evolved thanks to an extremely rare ore found in volcanic areas.

name: Ursaluna
description: I believe it was Hisui's swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.

name: Basculegion
description: This Pokémon is cloaked in the souls of its comrades who perished during a punishing journey to the river of their birth.

name: Sneasler
description: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.

name: Overqwil
description: Overqwil's poisonous spikes will reflexively react even while Overqwil sleeps, stabbing any moving thing that approaches.

name: Enamorus
description: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokémon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

name: Sprigatito
description: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

name: Floragato
description: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

name: Meowscarada
description: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

name: Fuecoco
description: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

name: Crocalor
description: The combination of Crocalor's fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokémon's head.

name: Skeledirge
description: The fiery bird changes shape when Skeledirge sings. Rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on Skeledirge's head gained a soul.

name: Quaxly
description: Its strong legs let it easily swim around in even fast-flowing rivers. It likes to keep things tidy and is prone to overthinking things.

name: Quaxwell
description: These Pokémon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.

name: Quaquaval
description: A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. This Pokémon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.

name: Lechonk
description: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn't use it for anything other than foraging.

name: Oinkologne
description: Oinkologne is proud of its fine, glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.

name: Tarountula
description: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokémon's natural enemy.

name: Spidops
description: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.

name: Nymble
description: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it's in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Lokix
description: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.

name: Pawmi
description: It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

name: Pawmo
description: When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.

name: Pawmot
description: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

name: Tandemaus
description: Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.

name: Maushold
description: They build huge nests with many rooms that are used for different purposes, such as eating and sleeping.

name: Fidough
description: This Pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough's breath induces fermentation in the Pokémon's vicinity.

name: Dachsbun
description: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon's body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.

name: Smoliv
description: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

name: Dolliv
description: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

name: Arboliva
description: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.

name: Squawkabilly
description: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

name: Nacli
description: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.

name: Naclstack
description: This Pokémon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey's body.

name: Garganacl
description: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.

name: Charcadet
description: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

name: Armarouge
description: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.

name: Ceruledge
description: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.

name: Tadbulb
description: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

name: Bellibolt
description: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.

name: Wattrel
description: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

name: Kilowattrel
